Core, seed, and remove the white ribs from the @red bell pepper{1}(cored, seeded, and thinly sliced), then thinly slice. Mince or grate the @ginger{1%thumb}(minced) and @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Thinly slice the @scallions{2}(thinly sliced), keeping the whites and greens separate. Mince the @chili pepper{1}(minced). Slice the @shiitake mushrooms{4%oz}(sliced). Trim the @snow peas{4%oz}(trimmed).

Make the soy mixture: In a #small bowl{}, combine the @soy sauce{9%tsp} and @sugar{3%tbsp}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add the bell pepper and mushrooms and cook, tossing, for ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened and golden brown. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the snow peas and scallion whites and cook, tossing, for ~{3-4%minutes}, until the snow peas are tender.

Add the ginger, garlic, and a pinch of Thai chili (to taste) and cook, tossing, until fragrant for ~{1-2%minutes}. Add the soy mixture to the pan and cook for another ~{1%minute}, until slightly thickened.

Add the @egg noodles{9%oz} to the pan and toss to combine with the sauce and vegetables for ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a large drizzle of oil to the pan and cook, without stirring, until the noodles begin to crisp in the bottom of the pan.

Garnish with the scallion greens and @cashew pieces{1/4%cup}. Enjoy!

> The key to this dish is leaving the noodles to crisp up in the pan long enough. It might be tempting to stir, but try to resist! A sweet, gingery sauce is kicked up by a touch of spicy Thai chili for heat.